Defendant Matthew Phillip Stehr in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Matthew Phillip Stehr in custody.  
James C. Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNTS 2, 3, AND 4:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  3 1/2 YEARS ON EACH COUNT, CONSECUTIVE to each other and any other sentence; credit for 200 days on COUNT 2 ONLY. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 1 1/2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program ONLY AFTER SERVING 5 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety- no illegal drugs unless prescribed by physician;
*Cooperate with random urine screens- no positive results;
*No contact with known drug users or locations where illegal substances are trafficked or consumed;
*No contact with co-actor Govanni E. Martinez (dob 12-25-85);
*No contact with McDonald's, Subway, or Burger King stores within Milwaukee Metro Area-defined by the court as the following counties: Milwaukee, Waukesha, Racine, Ozaukee, and Washington;
*Participate in Cognitive behavior therapy program and any other programming deemed appropriate by the department/agent;
*Seek/maintain full time employment;
*COUNT 2 ONLY: If not previously done, provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of supervision period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court orders restitution in the stipulated amount of $354.25 to McDonald's located on Potter Ave., $536.00 to Subway located on S. 60th St, $498.00 to Subway located on S. 27th St.; joint and several with Govanni Martinez (15CF470).  The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession, Body armor possession, and Voting.  Defendant advised of dna consequences.  Appeal rights given.
